otherdetails.otherdetail:
- A supplication to Mary (Säʿali länä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl Maryam “Pray for us, Holy Virgin Mary...”) is written after Ps. 51 (fol. 51v, ls.3-13). It was written by the same scribe.
- In Text I-3: 
vacant line between Songs 1 and 2 (fol. 161v l.2), between Song 2 and 3 (fol. 162v l.9) and between Song 4 and 5 (fol. 167r l.18); 
only Songs 1 and 2 are numbered;
the number for Song 3 is missing: the space for the number (s. Songs 1 and 2) was left vacant by the copyst.
- In Text I-5: 
lacuna on fol. 181va ls. 12-13;
in the supplication formula at the end of the text, the names of the individuals (probably the donors) to whom the supplication is dedicated are missing.
A chain of black and red nine dot asterisks is at explicit of Text I-3 (fol. 168r).

txquiremarks.txquiremark:
- Quire marks are written in the upper margin (left side) of the first fol. of the quires: 
fol. 15r: ፪ “2”; 
fol. 25r: ፫ “3”; 
fol. 35r: ፬ “4”; 
fol. 45r: ፭ “5”; 
fol. 55r: ፮ “6”; 
fol. 67r: ፯ “7”; 
fol. 77r: ፰ “8”; 
fol. 87r: ፱ “9”; 
fol. 99r: ፲ “10”; 
fol. 109r: ፲፩ “11”; 
fol. 119r: ፲፪ “12”; 
fol. 129r: ፲፫ “13”; 
fol. 139r: ፲፬ “14”; 
fol. 149r: ፲፭ “15”; 
fol. 159r: ፲፮ “16”; 
fol. 169r: ፯ “7” (the number should be: ፲፯ “17”); 
fol. 179r: ፲፱ “19” (according to the sequence, the number is mistaken: it should be: ፲፰ “18”).
All the numbers are encircled by little black dashes.
